PEA showed that, 455 out of 535 genes were significantly enriched within 111 BP candidate pathways/gene sets (p-values < 1e-10, q = 0.001 for FDR; BP_GB→Related Pathways). Among these 111 pathways, 17 are related to the neuronal system (with 273 unique genes), 6 to brain function/development (75 unique genes), 5 to behavior (58 unique genes) and 1 to aging (50 unique genes). Due to the lack of space, we only present the top 10 pathways enriched in Table 1 (p-value ≤ 4.5e-36, including 268 out of 535 genes).Table 1
